Color the Console with a second txt file. Coloring as folows:
0 NONE (FOR BLACK)
1 FOREGROUND_BLUE
2 FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
3 FOREGROUND_GREEN 
4 FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
5 FOREGROUND_RED  
6 FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
7 FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_GREEN 
8 FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
9 FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_RED
A FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
B FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_GREEN 
C FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY
D 
E FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_BLUE
F FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY

Create 2 new vectors of char containing BG and FG information, the draw function will call the Winapi WriteConsoleOutputAtribute translating the char in colors
